<HEAD>STIRPIUM ORIENTALIUM. RARIORUM CATALOGI TRES.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="plants of Greece and Syria">
<PB REF="302">
<PB N="3" REF="302">
<HEAD>Stirpium Orientalium rariorum Catalogus, prae&s;ertim Graeciae, &amp; Syriae provinciis na&s;centium.</HEAD>
<DIV4 N="A" TYPE="section">
<HEAD>A.</HEAD>
<P>A Brotanum foemina verum Dio&s;coridis <HI>Zanoni v.</HI> He|liochry&s;um Abrotani foeminae facie.</P>
<P>Acaciae foliis frutex Me&s;apotamicus <HI>Col. Annot.</HI> in Res medicas <HI>Novae Hi&s;p. Recchi.</HI> A caciae &s;imilis Me|&s;opotamica, minuti&s;&s;imis foliis, &s;iliqua integra con|torta, cra&s;&s;a &amp; obtu&s;a, &s;eu Siliquae Nabathaea <HI>Breyn. Prod.</HI> 2. Juxta Tlgridem fluvium in Me&s;opotamia, &amp; Euphratem in Arabia de&s;erta.</P>
